commit.message:
Check for silent pyglet audio driver

Pyglet falls back to the SilentDriver when nothing is available
instead of throwing an exception, so check that and exit.

Also dropped the outdated audio driver preference to use pyglet default
selection, which allows for PulseAudio

Closes #44

Add LICENSE file and clarify GPL-2.0 or later

Previously there was no LICENSE file, but the header of brainworkshop.py
specified the project was under the GPL. The GPL itself says that if no
version is specified, it is allowed to use any GPL version.

To better clarify the license of the project for the users, as well as
to ensure the license will show up clearly on Github, xantares and I
have decided to officially give it GPL-2.0 or later.
